# PROMPT 

See, brother, I refactored the code from a single user to a multi-user 



In this situation, the user adds the access tokens manually, gets the api key, and then  gets the brand's info, and based on the unique brand ID -- the MCP servers get the credentials of the user and perform the task for the user 



So there is separate data in the DB for all the users -- not all users will see the same data as before this 





But now the problem is 



The user cannot manually get the secret tokens from the Shopify and Meta platforms and then add secrets there 



So, for this, the solution is OAuth 



e.g., example for connecting to meta 



User clicks "Connect Meta."

        ↓

Redirect → Meta OAuth (Facebook Login)

        ↓

User approves permissions (ads, Instagram, pages)

        ↓

Your backend gets access_token

        ↓

Store in DB per user

        ↓

Your custom ads-mcp / social-mcp uses that token

to call the Graph API on their behalf





Same thing with Shopify to get the access token and webhook secret 

